events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Tyrann Mathieu returned a punt 62 yards for a touchdown and set up two other scores with a fumble recovery and another dazzling return, leading No. 1 LSU to a 42-10 rout of Georgia in the Southeastern Conference championship game Saturday.

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Joseph Randle ran for 151 yards and two touchdowns, Richetti Jones returned a fumble for a score and No. 3 Oklahoma State throttled No. 13 Oklahoma 44-10 Saturday night to win the Big 12 championship and make its case to play for a national title.

events.name: New Mexico Lobos at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Kellen Moore threw three touchdowns in the final home game of his brilliant career and Doug Martin ran for two more as Boise State rolled over New Mexico 45-0 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moore sharp as Boise St. dominates New Mexico

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: John Hubert ran for 120 yards and the go-ahead touchdown, and Kansas State (No. 11 BCS, No. 16 AP) kept alive its chances for a share of the Big 12 championship with a 30-23 victory over Iowa State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas State edges Iowa State to earn 10th win

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Montee Ball ran for three touchdowns including the decisive 7-yard score with 3:45 to go, leading No. 15 Wisconsin past Michigan State (No. 13 BCS, No. 11 AP) 42-39 in the inaugural Big Ten championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, Wisconsin win Big Ten title

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw three touchdown passes and ran for another as Clemson routed Virginia Tech 38-10 Saturday night to win its first Atlantic Coast Conference championship in 20 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemson rips Va. Tech to win ACC

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III ran for two touchdowns and passed for two more to lead Baylor (No. 17 BCS, No. 19 AP) to a 48-24 win over Texas (No. 22 BCS), capping the Bears' best regular season in 25 years.

events.name: UNLV Rebels at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Greg McCoy returned a kickoff and Kris Gardner had an interception return for a touchdown in a 12-second span, and the 18th-ranked TCU Horned Frogs could bust into the BCS again after a 56-9 victory over UNLV in their Mountain West finale Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU wins easily, eyes BCS bid

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at Houston Cougars

headlines.description: Austin Davis threw four touchdown passes and No. 24 Southern Mississippi ruined Houston's perfect season and Bowl Championship Series hopes with a 49-28 victory over the Cougars (No. 6 BCS, No. 7 AP) on Saturday.

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Antwuan Reed returned a fumble 20 yards for a touchdown with less than 3 minutes remaining to lift Pittsburgh to a 33-20 win over Syracuse on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reed's fumble return TD lifts Pitt past Syracuse

events.name: Connecticut Huskies at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Munchie Legaux threw a career-high three touchdown passes on Saturday, and Cincinnati's defense got two scores of its own, setting up a 35-27 victory over Connecticut that left the Bearcats one of three teams sharing the Big East title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy drops UConn for share of Big East title
